def: The office duty of a trierarch.
An error committed in chronology by placing an event after itsreal time.
A German cavalry soldier of the fourteenth and fifteenthcenturies.
A driving wind; a wind that drives snow, sand, etc., intoheaps. Beau. & Fl.
Like a dunce; duncish.The most dull and duncical commissioner. Fuller.
Originally, a gondola race in Venice; now, a rowing or sailingrace, or a series of such races.
To madden; to rave. [Obs.]An infatuating and delirating spirit in it. Holland.
One of party opposed to a federative government; -- appliedparticularly to the party which opposed the adoption of theconstitution of the United States. Pickering.
